sql:
SELECT COUNT(setting_id) 
FROM exposure_settings 
WHERE lighting_condition = 'Sunny' AND iso = 100 AND shutter_speed = '1/125';

external_knowledge:
- "Highest ISO settings" refer to images with the maximum ISO value among their exposure settings;
- "Not recommended" means the image does not have any non-null or non-empty recommendations in the analysis;
- "More than one user session" indicates that the photographer has logged in more than once.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(link_id) 
FROM image_exposure_links 
WHERE image_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- 'Sunny' lighting condition implies bright outdoor conditions;
- 'f/2.8' aperture is a wide aperture setting, allowing more light into the camera;
- ISO 100 is a low sensitivity setting, typically used in bright conditions to minimize noise;
- 'Average analysis results' refer to the mean of the quality scores assigned to the images based on various criteria.

- 'Between the dawn of 2020 and the twilight of 2022' refers to the date range from January 1, 2020, to December 31, 2022;
- 'Found their way into the hands of photographers more than once' refers to images with the same title and photographer appearing more than once in the dataset;
- 'Repeated masterpieces' refers to images that have been recorded multiple times in the database.

sql:
SELECT setting_id, iso 
FROM exposure_settings 
WHERE lighting_condition = 'Sunny' AND shutter_speed = '1/125';

external_knowledge:
- "Best aperture setting" refers to the aperture value associated with the most recent image for each exposure setting;
- "Exposure settings" include the lighting condition, aperture, ISO, and shutter speed used when taking the image;
- "More than one image" means that the exposure setting has been used for at least two different images.

sql:
SELECT name
FROM photographers
ORDER BY name;

external_knowledge:
- "top 3 artists" refers to the photographers with the highest number of images;
- "captured the most moments" refers to the total number of distinct images taken by each photographer;
- "fine-tuned with exposure settings" refers to images that have associated exposure settings.

- "artists" refers to photographers;
- "works" refers to images;
- "scrutinized under the lens of analysis" refers to image analysis;
- "start of the new year" refers to the date after December 31, 2022.

- 'Admin' role refers to a specific user role in the system;
- 'Top-ranked' refers to the photographers who have taken the most images among those with the 'Admin' role;
- 'Titles' of images are the descriptive names or labels given to each image.

- "photographers" refers to individuals who take images;
- "images" are the photographs taken by the photographers;
- "total_images" is the count of all images a photographer has taken.
